Package org.ietf.nea.pt.serialize.reader.bytebuffer

IETF transport message byte buffer readers.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    PtTlsMessageErrorValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport error message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessageExperimentalValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport experimental message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessageHeaderReader
    Reader to parse a transport message header compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessagePbBatchValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport TNCCS batch message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessageSaslAuthenticationDataValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport SASL authentication data message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessageSaslMechanismSelectionValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport SASL mechanism selection message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessageSaslMechanismsValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport SASL mechanisms message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessageSaslResultValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport SASL result message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessageVersionRequestValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport version request message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsMessageVersionResponseValueReader
    Reader to parse a transport version response message value compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsReader
    Reader to parse an entire transport message compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
    PtTlsReaderFactory
    Factory utility to create a reader, that can parse an entire transport message compliant to RFC 6876 from a buffer of bytes to a Java object.
